olive oil
2 clove garlic
1 Brown Onion
1 carrot
1 tin sweetcorn
1 tin black beans
1 packet tomato paste
¼ cup water
½ tbs brown sugar
20 g plant-based butter
1 packet enchilada sauce
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet Plant-Based Mayo
1 sachet Mexican Fiesta spice blend

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Finely chop garlic. Thinly slice onion. Grate the
carrot.
• Drain the sweetcorn. Drain and rinse black
beans.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil
over medium-high heat. Cook onion and carrot
until tender, 2-3 minutes.
• SPICY! The spice blend is hot! Add less if you're
sensitive to heat. Add garlic, Mexican Fiesta
spice blend and tomato paste, stirring, until
fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add beans, the water, brown sugar and plant-based butter and cook, stirring, until thickened,
2-3 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat. Stir through half the
enchilada sauce until combined. Season to
taste.

• Lay mini flourtortillas on a flat surface. Spoon
bean filling down the centre of each tortilla.
• Roll tortillas up tightly and place, seam-side
down, evenly spaced on a lined oven tray. Drizzle
with olive oil and season with salt and pepper.
• Bake taquitos until golden and starting to crisp,
8-10 minutes.

• Meanwhile, roughly chop baby spinach leaves.
• Wipe out the frying pan, then return to
medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook sweetcorn until lightly browned,
4-5 minutes. Transfer to a medium bowl.

TIP: Cover the pan with a lid if the kernels are
“popping” out.

• To the bowl of charred corn, add baby spinach
leaves and a drizzle of olive oil.
• Toss to combine. Season to taste.

• Divide black bean taquitos between plates.
• Top with remaining enchilada sauce and corn
salsa.
• Drizzle over plant-based mayo to serve. Enjoy!